This is heaven. The cheesecake is a slice of heaven. The crust is gorgeous. Dulce de leche - home-made or store-bought - goes beautifully, as do strawberries and candied pecans, which are ridiculously easy to make AND go fantastically on other stuff too, like salads. (I made the whole recipe and about half of the pecans wound up on the salad and people went crazy). But this is an excellent recipe to be creative with, it lends itself to all kinds of flavors - the mascarpone, which basically tastes like milk, gives it a creamier, sweeter, milkier consistency... you cannot go wrong.

Rating: 4
This was divine! The cheesecake had a lovely creamy consistency and was delicious on it's own, but you must make the dulce de leche sauce. It was very easy to make, and the caramel flavor is sooooo good! I made the candied pecans and put them on the edge of the plate around the cake, then stood a few up on end in the middle of the cake. I then put plain toasted pecan halves around the edge of the cake itself, as I was afraid the candied pecans might be too sweet and also would soften onto the the cake. It received rave reviews, and was quite easy to make. Definitely use at least 3 layers of heavy duty foil to keep the water out of the cake. I used pecan shortbread cookies as well as the pecans in the crust (I'm originally from Texas, so I love pecans!) This is a wonderful recipe.

