I found this recipe to be quite simple to make and with a very good result. The cheesecake is delicious and creamy, yet not as heavy as some cheesecakes can be. Don't sub on the crust - it really makes this cake. Everyone commented on it. The candied pecans were easy to make and looked beautiful on the cake - however, don't put them on until the last minute. They will "bleed" onto the cake. The sauce, again, very easy to make and quite tasty, but really not needed for this recipe. The cake is perfectly good to stand on its own, it doesn't need the sauce to make it. The only downside I experienced was that the cake had little bubbles that burst during cook, so the top of my cake did not appear smooth. This didn't affect the taste, however, so no big deal. Overall, quite good and recommended!

