Rating: 4
OK, this is still doing the overnight chill thing in the fridge, so I haven't actually eaten a piece, but I tasted both crust and filling while I was making them and they both seemed great. But I can't imagine why anyone would use a mixer with this recipe -- if you have all the ingredients at room temp as they call for, it's so easy just to stir everything in. It's MUCH easier than Tollhouse cookies which I always mix by hand! I think the separation that other cooks have encountered is caused by 1. electric mixers at too high speed and/or 2. (and more likely) not having all ingredients at room temp. A cold egg beaten too quickly into a room temp filling could easily cause problems. It's the easiest filling I've ever mixed by hand (well, wooden spoon to be accurate). Taking it to New Year's tomorrow -- I'll let you know how people react to the finished product!

