Abby Dodge advises that she never had another problem with cheesecakes breaking or cracking when she set her mixer to LOW speed. Do not beat too much air into these things. I personally use a hand mixer on #2 to keep from overbeating my cheesecakes. Only mix until incorporated, don't overmix!!

Rating: 4
This was delicious! In response to the review before me I think it is important to know NOT to overbeat. I made this perfect the first time and the second time my mix also seperated. I needed this for a dinner party so I set out to make another one this time making only one change - I set my mixer (Kitchen Aid) on STIR (the first setting) and when I added new ingredients I would turn it on just until they were mixed well - then I would turn it off and add another ingredient. After all eggs were incorporated well - I turned the mixer off. I think if you overbeat it does cause seperation. The second cheesecake came out PERFECT! Everyone loved it!!

